---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Research | ByteLite LLC"
  description="ByteLite LLC conducts private deterministic systems research while keeping technical mechanisms intentionally non-public during validation."
  keywords="ByteLite LLC research, deterministic systems, private research, Helena Montana"
  
>
  <Header slot="header" />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="res-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Research</p>
      <h1>Private systems research.</h1>
      <p class="res-hero-sub">
        ByteLite LLC conducts private research into deterministic infrastructure,
        verification-focused systems, media tooling, and reasoning interfaces.
        Technical mechanisms are intentionally not public during validation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why it matters -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container res-why">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Why It Matters</p>
        <h2>The software stack needs better foundations.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="res-why-points">
        <div class="res-point">
          <h4 style="color:#e4e7f2;margin-bottom:.5rem;">Data growth is accelerating.</h4>
          <p>Storage, bandwidth, and infrastructure costs compound yearly. Systems built without deterministic foundations accumulate technical debt that compounds the same way.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="res-point">
          <h4 style="color:#e4e7f2;margin-bottom:.5rem;">Opacity is a risk.</h4>
          <p>Software systems that cannot be inspected cannot be trusted at scale. Deterministic, verifiable approaches reduce the inspection surface for critical infrastructure.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="res-point">
          <h4 style="color:#e4e7f2;margin-bottom:.5rem;">Privacy requires architecture, not policy.</h4>
          <p>Genuine privacy cannot be bolted onto systems built without it. It requires decisions at the architectural level from the start.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Research areas -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Research Areas</p>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:2.5rem;">What ByteLite LLC researches.</h2>
      <div class="res-areas-grid">
        <div class="card res-area-card">
          <div class="res-area-icon">&#9632;</div>
          <h3 style="color:#e4e7f2;margin:.75rem 0 .625rem;">Data Infrastructure</h3>
          <p>Deterministic data representation and verification. Private research into how data can be encoded, stored, and reconstructed with guaranteed properties. No public product available yet.</p>
          <div style="margin-top:1rem;"><span class="badge badge-research">Private research</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="card res-area-card">
          <div class="res-area-icon res-icon-blue">&#9632;</div>
          <h3 style="color:#e4e7f2;margin:.75rem 0 .625rem;">Verification Systems</h3>
          <p>Research into verifiable, inspectable system behavior. The goal is software that can be independently confirmed to do what it claims, without requiring trust in opaque implementations.</p>
          <div style="margin-top:1rem;"><span class="badge badge-research">Private research</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="card res-area-card">
          <div class="res-area-icon res-icon-amber">&#9632;</div>
          <h3 style="color:#e4e7f2;margin:.75rem 0 .625rem;">Media Tooling</h3>
          <p>Private research into consistent, controllable visual media workflows. No public product. Technical details not disclosed during active development.</p>
          <div style="margin-top:1rem;"><span class="badge badge-planned">Early research</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="card res-area-card">
          <div class="res-area-icon res-icon-purple">&#9632;</div>
          <h3 style="color:#e4e7f2;margin:.75rem 0 .625rem;">Reasoning Interfaces</h3>
          <p>Research into more inspectable software reasoning. Connected to the Deep Kore research project. Not a public AI product. See below for public stance.</p>
          <div style="margin-top:1rem;"><span class="badge badge-research">Private research</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Public boundary -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:760px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Public Boundary</p>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:1.25rem;">What is intentionally not public.</h2>
      <p style="font-size:1.0625rem;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
        Detailed technical mechanisms for all research areas are intentionally not public
        while development and validation continue. This is not unusual for early-stage private research.
      </p>
      <div class="boundary-box">
        <h4 style="color:#e4e7f2;margin-bottom:1rem;">No public claim exists for:</h4>
        <ul class="boundary-list">
          <li>A public production data infrastructure product</li>
          <li>A public API of any kind</li>
          <li>Published independent benchmark results</li>
          <li>A public media tooling product</li>
          <li>A public AI or reasoning system</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <p style="font-size:.9375rem;color:#555e7a;margin-top:1.5rem;">
        Research, partnership, and investor inquiries are welcome.
        Technical details are shared selectively under appropriate agreements.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Deep Kore section -->
  <section class="section" id="deep-kore">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:760px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Deep Kore / AIya</p>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:1.25rem;">Private reasoning research.</h2>
      <p style="font-size:1.0625rem;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
        Deep Kore is private reasoning research exploring more inspectable software behavior.
        AIya is the human-facing guide concept connected to that work.
      </p>
      <div class="deepkore-stance">
        <div class="stance-item">
          <span class="stance-no">&#10005;</span>
          <span>Not a public AI product</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stance-item">
          <span class="stance-no">&#10005;</span>
          <span>No architecture details are public</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stance-item">
          <span class="stance-yes">&#10003;</span>
          <span>Safety-first principles govern all research</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stance-item">
          <span class="stance-yes">&#10003;</span>
          <span>Research prototype — not a commercial product</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Contact CTA -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container cta-block-alt">
      <h2>Research, partnership, and investor inquiries.</h2>
      <p>Technical details are not public by default. To discuss research, partnership potential, or investment, contact directly.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Contact ByteLite LLC</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</Layout>

<style>

.res-hero {
  padding: 6rem 0 4.5rem;
  background: radial-gradient(ellipse 70% 50% at 50% -5%, rgba(99,102,241,.06) 0%, transparent 70%);
}
.res-hero h1 { max-width: 640px; }
.res-hero-sub { max-width: 600px; margin-top: 1.25rem; font-size: 1.0625rem; color: #7b829e; line-height: 1.75; }
.res-why { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.6fr; gap: 4rem; align-items: start; }
@media (max-width: 767px) { .res-why { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2rem; } }
.res-why-points { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2rem; }
.res-point {}
.res-areas-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 1.25rem; }
@media (max-width: 640px) { .res-areas-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
.res-area-card {}
.res-area-icon { font-size: .875rem; color: #6366f1; }
.res-icon-blue { color: #60a5fa; }
.res-icon-amber { color: #f59e0b; }
.res-icon-purple { color: #a78bfa; }
.boundary-box {
  background: #111828; border: 1px solid #1a2235; border-radius: .75rem; padding: 1.75rem;
}
.boundary-list { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: .625rem; }
.boundary-list li { font-size: .9375rem; color: #7b829e; padding-left: 1.25rem; position: relative; }
.boundary-list li::before { content: "—"; position: absolute; left: 0; color: #4a5068; }
.deepkore-stance { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: .875rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
.stance-item { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: .875rem; }
.stance-item span:last-child { font-size: .9375rem; color: #a0a8c0; }
.stance-no { color: #f87171; font-size: 1rem; flex-shrink: 0; width: 1.25rem; text-align: center; }
.stance-yes { color: #34d399; font-size: 1rem; flex-shrink: 0; width: 1.25rem; text-align: center; }
.cta-block-alt {
  background: #0d1120; border: 1px solid #1a2235; border-radius: 1rem;
  padding: 3.5rem; text-align: center;
}
.cta-block-alt h2 { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.cta-block-alt p { max-width: 480px; margin: 0 auto 2rem; font-size: 1.0625rem; }

</style>
